Torrential thunderstorms sent a flash

flood surging through a valley into this Ohio River town, killing at least 11 people, leaving 51 missing and scores of others homeless Friday, authorities said.
The governor declared a state of emergency, and dispatched about 50 National Guardsmen to the area.
The Federal Emergency Management Agency declared Belmont County, which includes Shadyside, and Jefferson and Franklin counties disaster areas, making federal aid available to residents.
Vogt said two bodies were found in the Ohio River and one was found in a field next to the river after water receded.
At least five houses along Wegee Creek were washed away, and two cars were floating in water in one of the basements.
